The paper discusses the use of quantum computing for optimization problems and the post-processing techniques used to improve the quality of solutions. This falls under the category of quantum computing and optimization, which is often classified under cs.ET (Emerging Technologies). Additionally, the paper discusses pairing heuristics, which is a common technique used in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The analysis of the strengths and weaknesses of the Multi Qubit Correction (MQC) algorithm involves a discussion of the performance of different optimization methods, which is related to the field of data mining (cs.DM). The comparison between MQC and the built-in optimization method offered by D-wave Systems involves the evaluation of different algorithms, which is related to the field of computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the results of experiments and the comparison of different methods, which is related to the field of machine learning (cs.LG).
